rwriter," as the case may be, bear to the aggregate offering price of the Shares. The relative fault of the Company and the Selling Stockholder, on the one hand, and the Underwriters or Wachovia in its capacity as a "qualified independent underwriter," as the case may be, on the other, shall be determined by reference to, among other things, whether the untrue or alleged untrue statement of a material fact or the omission or alleged omission to state a material fact relates to information supplied by the Company and the Selling Stockholder or by the Underwriters or Wachovia in its capacity as a "qualified independent underwriter," as the case may be, and the parties' relative intent, knowledge, access to information and opportunity to correct or prevent such statement or omission.
