     Effective October 21, 2010, Approach Resources Inc. (the "Company") entered into a ninth amendment (the "Ninth Amendment") to its Credit Agreement dated as of January 18, 2008 (as amended, the "Credit Agreement") by and among the Company and its subsidiary guarantors, the lenders and JPMorgan Chase Bank, N.A., as agent and lender.
     The Ninth Amendment (a) increased the borrowing base and lenders' aggregate commitment under the Credit Agreement to $150 million from $115 million; (b) appointed KeyBank National Association ("KeyBank") and BNP Paribas ("Paribas") as Documentation Agent and Syndication Agent, respectively; and (c) assigned a 3.33% interest in the rights and obligations of The Frost National Bank under the Credit Agreement to each of KeyBank and Paribas.
