paid by the indemnifying party. The indemnifying party shall not control (but may participate at its own expense in the defense of), and the Indemnitee shall be entitled to have sole control over, the defense or settlement, compromise, admission or acknowledgment of any Third Party Claim (i) as to which the indemnifying party fails to assume the defense within the Response Period or (ii) to the extent the Third Party Claim seeks an order, injunction or other equitable relief against the Indemnitee which, if successful, would materially adversely affect the business, operations, assets, or financial condition of the Indemnitee
