Item 5.02 Departure of Directors or Certain Officers; Election of Directors; Appointment of Certain Officers; Compensatory Arrangements of Certain Officers.
(c) Appointment of Principal Operating Officer
On December 4, 2012, the Board of Directors of Approach Resources Inc. (the "Company") promoted Qingming Yang to Chief Operating Officer, effective immediately. Dr. Yang, age 49, has served as Executive Vice President  Business Development & Geosciences since November 2010. Dr. Yang joined the Company in July 2009 as the Company's Vice President  Exploration. Before joining Approach, Dr. Yang was employed by Pioneer Natural Resources for 12 years in a variety of positions, including Exploration Manager for Worldwide Exploration and Business Development, Geosciences Advisor and Technical Lead for Pioneer's Eagle Ford Shale team. Dr. Yang earned his B.S. in Petroleum Geology from Chengdu University of Technology in the People's Republic of China, his M.A. in Geology from George Washington University and his Ph.D. in Structural Geology from the University of Texas at Dallas.
To date, there have been no changes to the employment agreement dated January 24, 2011 by and between Dr. Yang and the Company on account of Dr. Yang's promotion.
Item 7.01 Regulation FD Disclosure.
On December 12, 2012, the Company announced the promotion of Qingming Yang to Chief Operating Officer. A copy of the press release is furnished herewith as Exhibit 99.1.
Item 9.01 Financial Statements and Exhibits.
 
 
